Updates on Most Active Stock: Harmony Gold Mining Co. Ltd (NYSE:HMY)


		Autor: Francisco Burgo ; Última actualización: 06 Junio , 2017 17:11:26 




Ajustar
Comentario
Impresión



The last session's volume of 3.89 million shares was higher than its average volume of 6.89 million shares. Harmony Gold Mining Company Limited (HMY) shares have been seen trading -60.78% off its 52 week- peak value and changed 2.69% from its 52 week-bottom price value. The "percentage off the 52-week high or low" refers to when a stock current price is relative to where it has traded over the last 52 weeks. This gives investors an idea of how much the security has moved in the a year ago and whether it is trading near the top, middle or bottom of the range.
JP Morgan "Downgrades" Harmony Gold Mining Co.Stock is now moving with a negative distance from the 200 day simple moving average of approximately -29.39%, and has a poor year to date (YTD) performance of -13.57% which means the stock is constantly subtracting to its value from the previous fiscal year end price. It is, therefore, best used with refinements to its application or in conjunction with other, confirming technical indicators.Analysts' mean recommendation for Harmony Gold Mining Company Limited (HMY) stands at 3.30.During last one month it showed the change of -9.48%. Its last month's stock price volatility remained 3.14% which for the week stands at 3.22%.Another critical number in evaluating a stock is P/E or the price to earnings ratio. The return on invested capital at 3.2%, which is good, compared to its peers. (ADR) (NYSE:HMY)'s 14-day RSI is presently at 27.60. Analyst rating score as published on FINVIZ are rated on a 1 to 5 scale. 1 is equivalent to a buy rating, 3 a hold rating, and 5 a sell rating. Harmony Gold Mining Company Limited (HMY) is a part of Basic Materials sector and belongs to Gold industry. The company have shares float of 432.93 million. Furthermore on 11/11/16 HSBC "Downgrades" the stock to Hold at $0. Closely-held shares are those owned by insiders, major shareholders and employees, while restricted stock refers to insider shares that can not be traded because of a temporary restriction such as the lock-up period after an initial public offering. A stock with a small float will generally be more volatile than a stock with a large float, apart from having limited liquidity and wider bid-ask spread. Because of these issues, institutional investors seldom invest in low-float stocks.The RSI is classified as a momentum oscillator, measuring the velocity and magnitude of directional price movements. The company's beta value is at -1.96. They use historic price data to observe stock price patterns to predict the direction of that price going forward. Ltd (NYSE:HMY)'s weekly and monthly volatility is 3.75%, 4.05% respectively.
 
 





