How Analysts Rated Harmony Gold Mining Co




				 08 Juillet, 2017,  11:07 | Author: Marc Bacque			












Analysts have placed a $2.56 price target on Harmony Gold Mining Company Limited, suggesting a 59.01% gain from recent close. The company has market cap of $708.47 million. Schroder Investment Management Group now owns 4,439,224 shares of the mining company's stock worth $10,388,000 after buying an additional 105,124 shares in the last quarter. Future earnings predictions are perhaps the most essential input when trying to value a company.
While looking at the Stock's Performance, Harmony Gold Mining Company Limited now shows a Weekly Performance of -1.8%, where Monthly Performance is -14.14%, Quarterly performance is -37.64%, 6 Months performance is -30.21% and yearly performance percentage is -60%.A number of other brokerages also recently commented on HMY. The stock has a beta value of -1.93. Over the last five days, shares have faced -4.73% losses and now is down -35.49% since hitting its 200-day moving average of $2.3.Price targets show what analysts believes a stock will be worth at the end of a certain time period. The stock presently has an average rating of "Hold" and a consensus target price of $2.50. The share last price represents downtick move of -40.52% in value from company's 52-Week high price and shows 0.39% above change in value from its 52-Week low price. The indicator should not be confused with relative strength. The quick ratio is more conservative than the current ratio because it excludes inventory and other current assets, which generally are more hard to turn into cash. The Company has a Return on Assets of -3.10%. The company was able to keep return on investment at 3.20% in the last twelve months. J P Morgan Chase & Co cut shares of Harmony Gold Mining Company Limited from an "overweight" rating to an "underweight" rating in a research report on Friday, March 3rd. As its institutional ownership stands at 33.50%, the ownership flows provide evidence to be a good test of stock returns. The company was maintained on Friday, July 29 by Scotia Capital.
